WEBVTT

00:10.314 --> 00:11.359
<i>Previously on</i> From...

00:11.489 --> 00:12.403
I hear their voices.

00:12.534 --> 00:15.015
Sara, just tell me
what you did.

00:15.145 --> 00:17.539
I left the door open.

00:17.669 --> 00:19.976
I have Sara tied up in
the basement of the church.

00:20.107 --> 00:21.282
Tell me you're joking.

00:21.412 --> 00:23.501
That girl may be the key to
unlocking all this.

00:23.632 --> 00:26.765
That girl may be
the way we all go home.

00:26.896 --> 00:28.680
Let's take a walk.

00:28.811 --> 00:29.681
We have to turn around!

00:29.812 --> 00:31.509
We can't be here!
Stop the bus!

00:31.640 --> 00:33.076
Everyone lease return
to your seats!

00:33.207 --> 00:34.643
Bad things are gonna
happen if--

00:36.775 --> 00:37.689
Stop the goddamn bus!

00:37.820 --> 00:39.517
Everyone on, right now.

00:39.648 --> 00:41.519
You're gonna get people killed,
you realize that?

00:41.650 --> 00:42.390
<i>Hello?</i>

00:42.520 --> 00:44.000
Where are you?

00:44.131 --> 00:46.263
<i>Is this Jim?</i>

00:46.394 --> 00:48.483
<i>Your wife shouldn't be
digging that hole, Jim.</i>

00:54.184 --> 00:57.405
You ever wonder
if Abby was right?

00:57.535 --> 00:59.363
What if it's all
just a dream?

01:00.582 --> 01:01.452
Aah!

01:03.498 --> 01:05.717
My blood is your blood now.

01:05.848 --> 01:07.197
Who was in my room?

01:07.328 --> 01:08.633
- Sorry?
- Someone was in my room,

01:08.764 --> 01:10.113
and they took something.

01:10.244 --> 01:11.375
Uh, I think I saw Jade

01:11.506 --> 01:12.724
and the Matthews boy
up here last night.

01:12.855 --> 01:13.682
You are not
listening to me.

01:13.812 --> 01:14.726
No, I am listening,

01:14.857 --> 01:16.250
and I'm telling you
to fuck off.

01:16.380 --> 01:18.643
Residents don't carry guns.
That's the rule.

01:18.774 --> 01:22.256
Well, uh, rules change.

01:22.386 --> 01:24.301
The wires aren't
connected to anything.

01:24.432 --> 01:26.390
They were just dangling
from the ceiling.

01:26.521 --> 01:29.350
Tabitha, we have
so much to talk about.

01:29.480 --> 01:31.308
I saw something
that wasn't there.

01:31.439 --> 01:32.222
What?

01:32.353 --> 01:33.745
I saw two children

01:33.876 --> 01:36.835
standing in the middle
of the road staring at me.

01:38.707 --> 01:40.709
Hello? Someone down here?

01:45.235 --> 01:46.541
Hi, Kenny.

01:51.894 --> 01:54.723
And right through here
we have the common area.

01:55.724 --> 01:59.249
And downstairs you'll have
a nice big room all to yourself.

01:59.380 --> 02:00.424
Come on in.

02:03.427 --> 02:04.689
No.

02:04.820 --> 02:07.388
I don't like it here.

02:07.518 --> 02:08.650
It's too sunny.

02:08.780 --> 02:11.218
I-I want to go home.

02:11.348 --> 02:12.915
No, no, Dad.
It's okay, look.

02:13.045 --> 02:14.743
Um, this place
is really nice.

02:14.873 --> 02:17.267
And, look, there's
a perfect little spot here

02:17.398 --> 02:19.226
for us to play chess.

02:19.356 --> 02:21.924
We stay here together?

02:24.361 --> 02:27.277
I'll give you folks
a few minutes, okay?

02:27.408 --> 02:28.713
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

02:38.593 --> 02:40.334
Look, Dad.

02:40.464 --> 02:43.206
Mom and I are gonna
be right down the street.

02:43.337 --> 02:47.297
You know? And we'll
come here every single day.

02:47.428 --> 02:49.560
But it's really, really
important for you

02:49.691 --> 02:52.433
to be somewhere where you
can't open the door at night.

02:55.784 --> 02:56.959
Dad, what happened last night...

02:58.700 --> 03:00.397
It's safer this way.

03:02.791 --> 03:04.575
No.

03:04.706 --> 03:05.707
I go home now.

03:28.512 --> 03:30.645
Uh, I'll go get
the rest of the stuff.

03:48.924 --> 03:50.752
Kenny.

03:50.882 --> 03:52.580
Sheriff Boyd, hey.

03:52.710 --> 03:53.842
Everything all right?

03:55.931 --> 03:59.239
Yeah, we were just, uh,
we're getting my dad settled in.

03:59.369 --> 04:00.762
I heard you had
a scare last night.

04:03.547 --> 04:05.288
Those things were knocking
on the door, they're--

04:06.898 --> 04:09.727
He was convinced that, uh,

04:09.858 --> 04:11.381
that his brothers
were outside.

04:11.512 --> 04:12.817
Right.

04:12.948 --> 04:15.994
My mom tried to stop him
but, uh, he-- he pushed her.

04:17.039 --> 04:18.997
It was, uh...

04:19.128 --> 04:20.695
Yeah, man, it's--

04:22.523 --> 04:23.437
It's hard.

04:24.960 --> 04:26.875
First time seeing
your parents struggle, huh?

04:29.356 --> 04:30.531
Yeah.

04:31.662 --> 04:32.707
You know, this place...

04:34.535 --> 04:36.406
...there's not a lot
holding it together.

04:37.146 --> 04:39.757
You know,
everyone is scared and confused,

04:39.888 --> 04:42.499
but a thing
I learned in the army,

04:42.630 --> 04:44.806
it always helps to
have people to look to--

04:44.936 --> 04:48.026
people who seem like they know
what the hell they're doing.

04:48.157 --> 04:49.724
That's really all
I'm trying to do here.

04:49.854 --> 04:51.856
Seems like you're doing
a really good job.

04:54.468 --> 04:56.774
I could use some help.

04:56.905 --> 04:59.081
Wouldn't mind having
a deputy watching my six.

05:02.127 --> 05:03.433
What do you say?

05:05.043 --> 05:06.480
You think?

05:07.872 --> 05:09.570
I think, right?

05:09.700 --> 05:11.006
Uh, yeah.

05:11.136 --> 05:12.094
I mean--

05:16.664 --> 05:17.621
Sheriff Boyd!

05:19.971 --> 05:20.972
I have to show you something.

05:21.103 --> 05:22.409
Can it wait?
I gotta--

05:22.539 --> 05:23.975
No, no, no.

05:24.106 --> 05:27.065
Um, I have--
I have to show you now.

05:30.634 --> 05:35.596
<i>" plays]</i>

05:40.775 --> 05:45.562
<i>♪ When I was just a little boy ♪</i>

05:45.693 --> 05:47.912
